\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You can assign any file or folder a custom icon via }{\f1\fs22\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Documents > Change Icon<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Some of the documents in this project have custom icons assigned, such as the folders using yellow book icons and the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93START HERE\u8221\'94 document, among others.}
